Speaking in July last year when the DFT made the announcement that £60 million of funding would be available for councils to bid for, MP for Scarborough and Whitby Robert Goodwill, who was then the Minister of State for Transport, said:

&quot;Green sustainable transport schemes cut congestion, improve air quality and can make it easier for people to get around more efficiently and effectively.

We are investing over £300 million to support cycling and walking schemes in this parliament, and this new scheme is aimed at kick-starting innovative and sustainable council projects.&quot;</content> 
